name: Victory Vocho
description:
To commemorate the fight for independence and self-determination in the lives of each of us.

The Angel of Independence is a Winged Victory sculpture on top of a column on a roundabout of Paseo de la Reforma Avenue, in Mexico City. It was built in 1910 to commemorate 100 years of the war of Independence from Spain.

During an earthquake on July 28, 1957, the sculpture fell to the ground and had to be restored after breaking into several pieces.

The process for the creation of this piece involved drawing, photography, and illustration.
